declare_parcel_as_script_with_stdin <<'/---'
Handle *return values* (i.e., standard output printed by runnables immediately
prior to returning to the caller).
/---

# ....................{ RETURNERS                          }....................
# See component "list" for related alias return_list().

:alias_command.declare 'string return_string(string text)'\
    '{
        get_stdin
        report_success
    } <<<' <<'/---'
Return the passed string from the current *runnable* (e.g., function, script).
Specifically, print such string to standard output and report *success* (i.e.,
zero exit status) from such runnable.
/---

# --------------------( WASTELANDS                         )--------------------
